<br>
I do a /who all gm and see that Vamin is on in Befallen, so i /petition and also send him and tell just to let him know that the situation was getting kinda out of hand.(Snicker fighting over an orc camp....)<br>
<br>
Well about 5 minutes later GM-Vamin comes into our camp and ask us what was going on. I explain that Scilentt was here camping the orcs for faction and DF Belts and that the guy from prism had moved into my camp told me I ws too high and told me to leave... I had even /reported when he told me that. The guy from Prism even backed my story.<br>
<br>
Vamin offers to have us share the spawn. Scilentt would pull 1 orc kill it then they would pull 1 orc and kill it ect... Now get this this guy from Prism actually asked the GM to pull for him since there group couldn't single pull and when he found out that the GM wouldn't do it then he decided that, no they didn't want to share the spawn with me.<br>
<br>
Heehee then the GM-Vamin decides that according to Verants policies all camps MUST be shared if anyone contest it, and since neiter of us were budging, he calls in Desilous to try and help with this situation. <br>
<br>
Desilous asked what was going on and the guy from Prism told him I was too high for the camp and that they were taking it. Well he said that if no decision could be reached then we would have to roll on the camp even after the Prism guy said I was there first....<br>
<br>
Needless to say we roll and i got a 16 out of 100 and lost the camp... BUt in the time that it took us to talk with the GM a 31 monk had moved into the camp and he was now claiming the camp... I tell the GM's that the 2 groups needed to roll on the camp again that it was "policy".<br>
<br>
I promptly get told to shut up and move along but not before Desilous decides that my name was against veriant policy and wipes my last name.<br>
<br>
